# dry-refactoring-workflow — History

## v1.12.0 (2026-06-30)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus #1427 — consolidate two coexisting log-format strings into named constants — /learn
**Verification:** verified-local (for the new Phase 12d; the rest of the skill is unchanged — `verified-ci` except the planning-only Phases 10/13/14/15 and the verified-local Phase 16)

### What changed

- Added Phase 12d (**VERIFIED-LOCAL** — EXECUTED end-to-end, not planning-only) — "A stale anchor
  can be a wrong FILENAME — and a strict-reviewed 'verified against disk' plan is NOT exempt." This
  extends Phase 12a (issue `Evidence:` sections go stale) from issue bodies to APPROVED
  implementation plans, and sharpens the failure mode: the rot is not only a wrong line number or a
  stale count, but a wrong FILENAME — because the named file may merely CALL the indirection root
  (a shared helper) where the literal actually lives.
- Captured from an EXECUTED ProjectHephaestus #1427 session: consolidate two coexisting log-format
  strings (`LOG_FORMAT` and the automation `[LEVEL] name:` format) into named constants
  `AUTOMATION_LOG_FORMAT` / `LOG_DATEFMT` in `hephaestus/constants.py`, routing all call sites
  through them.
- The concrete miss: the approved plan — graded "A / GO" with a strict review explicitly claiming
  "Verified accurate against disk" — said the drifted no-brackets variant lived at
  `hephaestus/automation/ensure_state_labels.py:189`. On disk that file had NO `format=` line at
  all; the real drifted literal lived at the indirection root `hephaestus/cli/utils.py:222` inside
  `configure_cli_logging()`, which `ensure_state_labels.main()` calls indirectly. Both the line
  number AND the filename were stale; only the symptom ("a no-brackets drift variant exists
  somewhere") was real. The plan also under-counted the per-module literals.
- Lesson: before editing, grep the CURRENT tree for the literal pattern the plan DESCRIBES
  (`grep -rn '<the literal>' src/`) — not the file it names — map the plan's INTENT onto the real
  call sites, and re-count every occurrence yourself (the count drifts like the `Evidence:`
  section). Fixing the indirection root (`configure_cli_logging`) transitively fixed the
  `ensure_state_labels` concern the plan was pointing at.
- Verification (verified-local): a single-source grep returning only the ONE canonical definition
  in `constants.py` (zero remaining literals in consumer modules); anti-drift parity tests asserting
  each consumer reads `constants.AUTOMATION_LOG_FORMAT`/`LOG_DATEFMT` rather than a literal; and the
  PRE-EXISTING behavioral suites staying green — full unit suite 5203 passed / 23 skipped, 87.22%
  coverage ≥ 83% gate, ruff clean, import-surface + automation-boundary guards green. Verified
  locally only; PR CI not yet merged at capture time.
- Added one Failed Attempts row (#1427 — trusted the plan's `ensure_state_labels.py:189` anchor), a
  Verified On entry (#1427), an Outcome bullet, a description item (17), and tags
  (`stale-plan-anchor`, `wrong-filename-anchor`, `indirection-root`, `grep-current-state`,
  `verified-against-disk-not-exempt`, `log-format-constants`, `configure-cli-logging`). Bumped
  frontmatter `version` 1.11.0 → 1.12.0; `date` stays 2026-06-30; frontmatter `verification` stays
  `unverified` (Phase 12d carries its own inline `verified-local` label, matching the v1.10.0+
  convention).

### Snapshot of the prior version

The complete v1.11.0 skill body is preserved in this history below (next entry). v1.12.0 is a
purely additive amendment: it adds Phase 12d, one Failed Attempts row, a Verified On row, an
Outcome entry, a description item, and tags. No prior content was removed or altered.

## v1.11.0 (2026-06-30)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus #1420 — deprecated `get_config_value()`/`retry_with_jitter()` removal — /learn
**Verification:** verified-local (for the new Phase 16; the rest of the skill is unchanged — `verified-ci` except the planning-only Phases 10/13/14/15)

### What changed

- Added Phase 16 (**VERIFIED-LOCAL** — EXECUTED end-to-end, not planning-only) — deprecated
  public-API symbol removal across ALL surfaces. Eight sub-sections:
  - 16a: Enumerate ALL surfaces before claiming removal — a deprecated public symbol lives on far
    MORE surfaces than its definition: (a) impl in the module, (b) subpackage `__init__.py` import
    line AND `__all__`, (c) top-level package lazy-loader map (`hephaestus/__init__.py`'s
    `_LAZY_IMPORTS`) + `__all__`, (d) deprecation-warning INFRASTRUCTURE (a `_DEPRECATED_LAZY` dict
    + the `__getattr__` branch that emits the access-time warning — and SIMPLIFY `__getattr__` once
    the last deprecated lazy symbol is gone), (e) tests, (f) docs. A module-source-only grep finds
    surface (a) and misses the other five.
  - 16b: Discovery-first repo-wide grep; classify every hit (def / re-export / lazy-map /
    deprecation-infra / test / doc); confirm ZERO runtime callers before treating it as a pure
    removal.
  - 16c: TDD absence-guard tests FIRST (the inversion to watch) — assert `not hasattr(module,
    symbol)`, `symbol not in pkg.__all__`, `symbol not in hephaestus._LAZY_IMPORTS`, `symbol not in
    dir(pkg)`. These FAIL first (symbol still present) → real RED. For the top-level guard, bust the
    PEP 562 cache with `pkg.__dict__.pop(symbol, None)` and wrap the `hasattr`/`dir` checks in
    `warnings.catch_warnings()` + `simplefilter("ignore", DeprecationWarning)`.
  - 16d: DELETE deprecation-GUARD test files outright (`test_deprecation_warnings.py`,
    `test_docs_deprecation_sync.py`) — a trimmed version asserts nothing and rots. Delete the
    per-symbol deprecated test CLASS (`TestGetConfigValue`, `TestRetryWithJitter`) in mixed files
    and prune the symbol from those files' imports — but RE-GREP first to confirm `patch`/
    `MagicMock` are still used elsewhere (they usually are).
  - 16e: Repoint integration fixtures that USE the symbol (e.g. a `test_dir_does_not_import_or_warn`
    that pops the symbol from `__dict__`) onto a NON-deprecated lazy symbol (`retry_with_backoff`)
    so the cache-bust path is still exercised; add a parametrized `REMOVED_DEPRECATED_SYMBOLS`
    absence guard alongside `TOP_LEVEL_SYMBOLS` and remove the symbol from the positive lists.
  - 16f: Docs are multi-location — COMPATIBILITY.md (flat lazy-symbol prose list + "Deprecated
    lazy-loaded symbols" callout + per-subpackage table ROW with `**(deprecated)**` + per-subpackage
    "Deprecated symbols" callout), MIGRATION.md (convert "Deprecated symbols" → "Removed deprecated
    symbols" table noting the BREAKING `ImportError`/`AttributeError`), ROADMAP.md (scrub stale
    examples).
  - 16g: Three-tier grep gauntlet — (1) package source clean; (2) docs clean EXCEPT
    `docs/MIGRATION.md`; (3) repo-wide excluding tests + MIGRATION.md (the reviewer's repo-wide
    stale-reference check) — then focused tests → `ruff check` → full suite green above the gate.
  - 16h: Treat as a BREAKING public-API removal — name the exact broken import forms in the PR body
    (`from pkg.config import get_config_value`, `from pkg.utils import retry_with_jitter`,
    `pkg.get_config_value`, `pkg.retry_with_jitter`) and record the rollback path (restore shims,
    re-add `__init__` exports + lazy map + deprecation infra, restore guard tests, revert docs).
- Added 3 Failed Attempts rows (removed-only-def-and-__all__, edited-instead-of-deleted-the-guard,
  ran-only-the-module-source-grep).
- Added a Verified On entry for ProjectHephaestus #1420 marked `verified-local`.
- Added trigger phrases and tags (`deprecated-api-removal`, `breaking-change`, `lazy-loader`,
  `lazy-imports`, `deprecation-guard-test`, `pep-562`, `all-surfaces`, `absence-guard-test`,
  `repo-wide-grep-gauntlet`, `compatibility-doc`, `migration-doc`).
- Bumped frontmatter `version` to 1.11.0 and `date` to 2026-06-30. Frontmatter `verification` stays
  `unverified` (per the v1.10.0 convention of marking per-phase verification inline); Phase 16
  carries its own `verified-local` label inline.

### Why

ProjectHephaestus issue #1420 was an EXECUTED (not planning-only) session that removed two deprecated
public functions — `get_config_value()` (`hephaestus/config`) and `retry_with_jitter()`
(`hephaestus/utils`) — that already emitted `DeprecationWarning`. The durable, reusable insight is
that a deprecated public symbol lives on far MORE surfaces than its definition (subpackage re-exports,
the top-level `_LAZY_IMPORTS` lazy-loader, the `_DEPRECATED_LAZY`/`__getattr__` deprecation
infrastructure, dedicated deprecation-guard test files, and multi-location docs), so a
module-source-only grep leaves half of them behind; the TDD shape inverts to absence guards (assert
the symbol is GONE, real RED), with a PEP 562 cache-bust required for the top-level guard;
deprecation-guard test files must be DELETED not trimmed; and the removal is a BREAKING public-API
change that must be declared. Verification was the full LOCAL suite (5535 passed / 24 skipped,
87.18% coverage ≥ the 83% gate), `ruff check` clean, and the three-tier repo-wide stale-reference
grep gauntlet empty; the PR's CI had not merged at capture time, so this phase is `verified-local`,
not `verified-ci`.

